    public class Enemy
extends java.lang.Object
implements Entity, java.io.Serializable
    This class represents an enemy in the game. This class takes certain commands but most actions from this class is randomized.

      • serialVersionUID

        private static final long serialVersionUID
        This field represents the unique ID used for saving and loading via serialization.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • visible

        private boolean visible
        This field represents whether the ninja is visible on the map. This field is set to false when the class is initialized and can only be set to true with the method setVisible() when the game is started in debug mode.

      • hasMoved

        private boolean hasMoved
        This field represents whether the ninja has moved during the turn where each ninja is moved around. This field makes sure that each ninja only moves once per turn. This field is set to false when the class is initialized and can be set to true with the method move() when the enemy has moved and false with the method resetTurn() at the start of the enemies' turn.
